line: How do you, Desdemona?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Well, my good lord.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Give me your hand: this hand is moist, my lady.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: It yet hath felt no age nor known no sorrow.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: This argues fruitfulness and liberal heart:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Hot, hot, and moist: this hand of yours requires

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: A sequester from liberty, fasting and prayer,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Much castigation, exercise devout;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: For here's a young and sweating devil here,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That commonly rebels. 'Tis a good hand,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: A frank one.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: You may, indeed, say so;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: For 'twas that hand that gave away my heart.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: A liberal hand: the hearts of old gave hands;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: But our new heraldry is hands, not hearts.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I cannot speak of this. Come now, your promise.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What promise, chuck?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I have sent to bid Cassio come speak with you.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I have a salt and sorry rheum offends me;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Lend me thy handkerchief.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Here, my lord.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That which I gave you.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I have it not about me.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Not?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: No, indeed, my lord.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That is a fault.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That handkerchief

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Did an Egyptian to my mother give;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: She was a charmer, and could almost read

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The thoughts of people: she told her, while

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: she kept it,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: 'Twould make her amiable and subdue my father

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Entirely to her love, but if she lost it

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Or made gift of it, my father's eye

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Should hold her loathed and his spirits should hunt

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: After new fancies: she, dying, gave it me;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And bid me, when my fate would have me wive,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: To give it her. I did so: and take heed on't;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Make it a darling like your precious eye;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: To lose't or give't away were such perdition

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: As nothing else could match.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Is't possible?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: 'Tis true: there's magic in the web of it:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: A sibyl, that had number'd in the world

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The sun to course two hundred compasses,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: In her prophetic fury sew'd the work;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The worms were hallow'd that did breed the silk;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And it was dyed in mummy which the skilful

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Conserved of maidens' hearts.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Indeed! is't true?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Most veritable; therefore look to't well.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Then would to God that I had never seen't!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ha! wherefore?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Why do you speak so startingly and rash?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Is't lost? is't gone? speak, is it out

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: o' the way?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Heaven bless us!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Say you?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: It is not lost; but what an if it were?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: How!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I say, it is not lost.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Fetch't, let me see't.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Why, so I can, sir, but I will not now.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: This is a trick to put me from my suit:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Pray you, let Cassio be received again.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Fetch me the handkerchief: my mind misgives.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Come, come;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: You'll never meet a more sufficient man.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The handkerchief!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I pray, talk me of Cassio.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The handkerchief!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: A man that all his time

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Hath founded his good fortunes on your love,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Shared dangers with you,--

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The handkerchief!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: In sooth, you are to blame.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Away!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Is not this man jealous?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I ne'er saw this before.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Sure, there's some wonder in this handkerchief:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I am most unhappy in the loss of it.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: 'Tis not a year or two shows us a man:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: They are all but stomachs, and we all but food;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: To eat us hungerly, and when they are full,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: They belch us. Look you, Cassio and my husband!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: There is no other way; 'tis she must do't:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: And, lo, the happiness! go, and importune her.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: How now, good Cassio! what's the news with you?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Madam, my former suit: I do beseech you

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: That by your virtuous means I may again

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Exist, and be a member of his love

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Whom I with all the office of my heart

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Entirely honour: I would not be delay'd.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: If my offence be of such mortal kind

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: That nor my service past, nor present sorrows,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Nor purposed merit in futurity,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Can ransom me into his love again,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: But to know so must be my benefit;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: So shall I clothe me in a forced content,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: And shut myself up in some other course,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: To fortune's alms.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Alas, thrice-gentle Cassio!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: My advocation is not now in tune;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: My lord is not my lord; nor should I know him,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Were he in favour as in humour alter'd.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: So help me every spirit sanctified,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: As I have spoken for you all my best

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And stood within the blank of his displeasure

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: For my free speech! you must awhile be patient:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: What I can do I will; and more I will

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Than for myself I dare: let that suffice you.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Is my lord angry?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: He went hence but now,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And certainly in strange unquietness.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Can he be angry? I have seen the cannon,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: When it hath blown his ranks into the air,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: And, like the devil, from his very arm

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Puff'd his own brother:--and can he be angry?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Something of moment then: I will go meet him:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: There's matter in't indeed, if he be angry.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I prithee, do so.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Something, sure, of state,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Either from Venice, or some unhatch'd practise

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Made demonstrable here in Cyprus to him,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Hath puddled his clear spirit: and in such cases

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Men's natures wrangle with inferior things,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Though great ones are their object. 'Tis even so;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: For let our finger ache, and it indues

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Our other healthful members even to that sense

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Of pain: nay, we must think men are not gods,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Nor of them look for such observances

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: As fit the bridal. Beshrew me much, Emilia,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I was, unhandsome warrior as I am,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Arraigning his unkindness with my soul;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: But now I find I had suborn'd the witness,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And he's indicted falsely.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Pray heaven it be state-matters, as you think,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And no conception nor no jealous toy

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Concerning you.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Alas the day! I never gave him cause.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: But jealous souls will not be answer'd so;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: They are not ever jealous for the cause,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: But jealous for they are jealous: 'tis a monster

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Begot upon itself, born on itself.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Heaven keep that monster from Othello's mind!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Lady, amen.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I will go seek him. Cassio, walk hereabout:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: If I do find him fit, I'll move your suit

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And seek to effect it to my uttermost.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I humbly thank your ladyship.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Save you, friend Cassio!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: What make you from home?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: How is it with you, my most fair Bianca?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I' faith, sweet love, I was coming to your house.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: And I was going to your lodging, Cassio.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: What, keep a week away? seven days and nights?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Eight score eight hours? and lovers' absent hours,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: More tedious than the dial eight score times?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: O weary reckoning!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Pardon me, Bianca:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I have this while with leaden thoughts been press'd:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: But I shall, in a more continuate time,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Strike off this score of absence. Sweet Bianca,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Take me this work out.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: O Cassio, whence came this?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: This is some token from a newer friend:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: To the felt absence now I feel a cause:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Is't come to this? Well, well.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Go to, woman!

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Throw your vile guesses in the devil's teeth,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: From whence you have them. You are jealous now

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: That this is from some mistress, some remembrance:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: No, in good troth, Bianca.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Why, whose is it?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I know not, sweet: I found it in my chamber.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I like the work well: ere it be demanded--

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: As like enough it will--I'ld have it copied:

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Take it, and do't; and leave me for this time.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Leave you! wherefore?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I do attend here on the general;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: And think it no addition, nor my wish,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: To have him see me woman'd.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Why, I pray you?

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Not that I love you not.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: But that you do not love me.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: I pray you, bring me on the way a little,

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: And say if I shall see you soon at night.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: 'Tis but a little way that I can bring you;

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: For I attend here: but I'll see you soon.

scene: SCENE IV.  Before the castle.
speaker: BIANCA
line: 'Tis very good; I must be circumstanced.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Will you think so?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Think so, Iago!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: What,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: To kiss in private?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: An unauthorized kiss.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Or to be naked with her friend in bed

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: An hour or more, not meaning any harm?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Naked in bed, Iago, and not mean harm!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It is hypocrisy against the devil:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: They that mean virtuously, and yet do so,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The devil their virtue tempts, and they tempt heaven.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: So they do nothing, 'tis a venial slip:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: But if I give my wife a handkerchief,--

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What then?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Why, then, 'tis hers, my lord; and, being hers,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: She may, I think, bestow't on any man.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: She is protectress of her honour too:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: May she give that?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Her honour is an essence that's not seen;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: They have it very oft that have it not:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: But, for the handkerchief,--

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: By heaven, I would most gladly have forgot it.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Thou said'st, it comes o'er my memory,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: As doth the raven o'er the infected house,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Boding to all--he had my handkerchief.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Ay, what of that?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That's not so good now.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: What,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: If I had said I had seen him do you wrong?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Or heard him say,--as knaves be such abroad,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Who having, by their own importunate suit,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Or voluntary dotage of some mistress,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Convinced or supplied them, cannot choose

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: But they must blab--

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Hath he said any thing?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: He hath, my lord; but be you well assured,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: No more than he'll unswear.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What hath he said?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: 'Faith, that he did--I know not what he did.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What? what?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Lie--

line: With her, on her; what you will.

speaker: OTHELLO

speaker: OTHELLO
line: --Handkerchief--confessions--handkerchief!--To

speaker: OTHELLO
line: confess, and be hanged for his labour;--first, to be

speaker: OTHELLO
line: hanged, and then to confess.--I tremble at it.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Nature would not invest herself in such shadowing

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: passion without some instruction. It is not words

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: that shake me thus. Pish! Noses, ears, and lips.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: --Is't possible?--Confess--handkerchief!--O devil!--

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Work on,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: My medicine, work! Thus credulous fools are caught;

speaker: IAGO
line: And many worthy and chaste dames even thus,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: All guiltless, meet reproach. What, ho! my lord!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: My lord, I say! Othello!

speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO
line: My lord is fall'n into an epilepsy:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.

speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: He will recover straight: when he is gone,

speaker: IAGO
line: I would on great occasion speak with you.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: How is it, general? have you not hurt your head?

speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

speaker: OTHELLO
line: A horned man's a monster and a beast.

speaker: IAGO
line: There's many a beast then in a populous city,

speaker: IAGO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Did he confess it?

speaker: IAGO
line: Good sir, be a man;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Think every bearded fellow that's but yoked

speaker: IAGO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO
line: Which they dare swear peculiar: your case is better.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: O, 'tis the spite of hell, the fiend's arch-mock,

speaker: IAGO
line: To lip a wanton in a secure couch,

speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

speaker: OTHELLO

speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO
line: Confine yourself but in a patient list.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO
line: A passion most unsuiting such a man--

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Cassio came hither: I shifted him away,

speaker: IAGO
line: And laid good 'scuse upon your ecstasy,

speaker: IAGO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: The which he promised. Do but encave yourself,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: And mark the fleers, the gibes, and notable scorns,

speaker: IAGO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

speaker: OTHELLO
line: Dost thou hear, Iago?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I will be found most cunning in my patience;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: That's not amiss;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: But yet keep time in all. Will you withdraw?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Now will I question Cassio of Bianca,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: A housewife that by selling her desires

speaker: IAGO
line: Buys herself bread and clothes: it is a creature

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: He, when he hears of her, cannot refrain

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO

speaker: IAGO
line: As he shall smile, Othello shall go mad;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: And his unbookish jealousy must construe

speaker: IAGO
line: Poor Cassio's smiles, gestures and light behavior,

speaker: IAGO
line: Quite in the wrong. How do you now, lieutenant?

speaker: CASSIO

speaker: IAGO

line: Now, if this suit lay in Bianco's power,

speaker: CASSIO
line: Alas, poor caitiff!

speaker: IAGO
line: I never knew woman love man so.

speaker: OTHELLO

speaker: OTHELLO

speaker: CASSIO
line: Ha, ha, ha!

speaker: OTHELLO
line: Do you triumph, Roman? do you triumph?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I marry her! what? a customer! Prithee, bear some

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. Before the castle.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Ha, ha, ha!

speaker: IAGO

speaker: OTHELLO

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: What place? what time? what form? what likelihood?

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: The Moor's abused by some most villanous knave,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Some base notorious knave, some scurvy fellow.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O heaven, that such companions thou'ldst unfold,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And put in every honest hand a whip

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: To lash the rascals naked through the world

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Even from the east to the west!

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Speak within door.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O, fie upon them! Some such squire he was

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: That turn'd your wit the seamy side without,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And made you to suspect me with the Moor.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: You are a fool; go to.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: O good Iago,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: What shall I do to win my lord again?

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Good friend, go to him; for, by this light of heaven,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I know not how I lost him. Here I kneel:

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: If e'er my will did trespass 'gainst his love,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Either in discourse of thought or actual deed,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Or that mine eyes, mine ears, or any sense,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Delighted them in any other form;

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Or that I do not yet, and ever did.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And ever will--though he do shake me off

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: To beggarly divorcement--love him dearly,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Comfort forswear me! Unkindness may do much;

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And his unkindness may defeat my life,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: But never taint my love. I cannot say 'whore:'

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: It does abhor me now I speak the word;

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: To do the act that might the addition earn

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Not the world's mass of vanity could make me.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: I pray you, be content; 'tis but his humour:

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: The business of the state does him offence,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: And he does chide with you.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: If 'twere no other--

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: 'Tis but so, I warrant.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Hark, how these instruments summon to supper!

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: The messengers of Venice stay the meat;

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Go in, and weep not; all things shall be well.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: How now, Roderigo!

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: I do not find that thou dealest justly with me.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: What in the contrary?

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: Every day thou daffest me with some device, Iago;

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: and rather, as it seems to me now, keepest from me

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: all conveniency than suppliest me with the least

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: advantage of hope. I will indeed no longer endure

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: it, nor am I yet persuaded to put up in peace what

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: already I have foolishly suffered.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Will you hear me, Roderigo?

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: 'Faith, I have heard too much, for your words and

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: performances are no kin together.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: You charge me most unjustly.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: With nought but truth. I have wasted myself out of

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: my means. The jewels you have had from me to

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: deliver to Desdemona would half have corrupted a

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: votarist: you have told me she hath received them

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: and returned me expectations and comforts of sudden

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: respect and acquaintance, but I find none.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Well; go to; very well.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: Very well! go to! I cannot go to, man; nor 'tis

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: not very well: nay, I think it is scurvy, and begin

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: to find myself fobbed in it.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Very well.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: I tell you 'tis not very well. I will make myself

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: known to Desdemona: if she will return me my

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: jewels, I will give over my suit and repent my

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: unlawful solicitation; if not, assure yourself I

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: will seek satisfaction of you.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: You have said now.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: Ay, and said nothing but what I protest intendment of doing.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Why, now I see there's mettle in thee, and even from

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: this instant to build on thee a better opinion than

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: ever before. Give me thy hand, Roderigo: thou hast

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: taken against me a most just exception; but yet, I

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: protest, I have dealt most directly in thy affair.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: It hath not appeared.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: I grant indeed it hath not appeared, and your

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: suspicion is not without wit and judgment. But,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Roderigo, if thou hast that in thee indeed, which I

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: have greater reason to believe now than ever, I mean

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: purpose, courage and valour, this night show it: if

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: thou the next night following enjoy not Desdemona,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: take me from this world with treachery and devise

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: engines for my life.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: Well, what is it? is it within reason and compass?

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Sir, there is especial commission come from Venice

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: to depute Cassio in Othello's place.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: Is that true? why, then Othello and Desdemona

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: return again to Venice.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: O, no; he goes into Mauritania and takes away with

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: him the fair Desdemona, unless his abode be

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: lingered here by some accident: wherein none can be

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: so determinate as the removing of Cassio.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: How do you mean, removing of him?

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Why, by making him uncapable of Othello's place;

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: knocking out his brains.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: And that you would have me to do?

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: Ay, if you dare do yourself a profit and a right.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: He sups to-night with a harlotry, and thither will I

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: go to him: he knows not yet of his horrorable

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: fortune. If you will watch his going thence, which

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: I will fashion to fall out between twelve and one,

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: you may take him at your pleasure: I will be near

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: to second your attempt, and he shall fall between

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: us. Come, stand not amazed at it, but go along with

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: me; I will show you such a necessity in his death

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: that you shall think yourself bound to put it on

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: him. It is now high suppertime, and the night grows

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: to waste: about it.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: I will hear further reason for this.

scene: SCENE II.  A room in the castle.
speaker: IAGO
line: And you shall be satisfied.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: I do beseech you, sir, trouble yourself no further.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O, pardon me: 'twill do me good to walk.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Madam, good night; I humbly thank your ladyship.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Your honour is most welcome.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Will you walk, sir?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O,--Desdemona,--

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: My lord?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Get you to bed on the instant; I will be returned

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: forthwith: dismiss your attendant there: look it be done.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I will, my lord.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: How goes it now? he looks gentler than he did.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: He says he will return incontinent:

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: He hath commanded me to go to bed,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And bade me to dismiss you.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Dismiss me!

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: It was his bidding: therefore, good Emilia,.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Give me my nightly wearing, and adieu:

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: We must not now displease him.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I would you had never seen him!

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: So would not I my love doth so approve him,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: That even his stubbornness, his cheques, his frowns--

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Prithee, unpin me,--have grace and favour in them.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I have laid those sheets you bade me on the bed.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: All's one. Good faith, how foolish are our minds!

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: If I do die before thee prithee, shroud me

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: In one of those same sheets.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Come, come you talk.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: My mother had a maid call'd Barbara:

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: She was in love, and he she loved proved mad

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And did forsake her: she had a song of 'willow;'

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: An old thing 'twas, but it express'd her fortune,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And she died singing it: that song to-night

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Will not go from my mind; I have much to do,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: But to go hang my head all at one side,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And sing it like poor Barbara. Prithee, dispatch.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Shall I go fetch your night-gown?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: No, unpin me here.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: This Lodovico is a proper man.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: A very handsome man.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: He speaks well.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I know a lady in Venice would have walked barefoot

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: to Palestine for a touch of his nether lip.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Singing  The poor soul sat sighing by a sycamore tree,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Sing all a green willow:

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Her hand on her bosom, her head on her knee,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Sing willow, willow, willow:

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: The fresh streams ran by her, and murmur'd her moans;

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Sing willow, willow, willow;

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Her salt tears fell from her, and soften'd the stones;

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Lay by these:--

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Sing willow, willow, willow;

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Prithee, hie thee; he'll come anon:--

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Sing all a green willow must be my garland.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Let nobody blame him; his scorn I approve,-

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Nay, that's not next.--Hark! who is't that knocks?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: It's the wind.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Singing  I call'd my love false love; but what

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: said he then?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Sing willow, willow, willow:

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: If I court moe women, you'll couch with moe men!

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: So, get thee gone; good night Ate eyes do itch;

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Doth that bode weeping?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: 'Tis neither here nor there.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I have heard it said so. O, these men, these men!

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Dost thou in conscience think,--tell me, Emilia,--

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: That there be women do abuse their husbands

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: In such gross kind?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: There be some such, no question.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Wouldst thou do such a deed for all the world?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Why, would not you?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: No, by this heavenly light!

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Nor I neither by this heavenly light;

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I might do't as well i' the dark.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Wouldst thou do such a deed for all the world?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: The world's a huge thing: it is a great price.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: For a small vice.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: In troth, I think thou wouldst not.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: In troth, I think I should; and undo't when I had

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: done. Marry, I would not do such a thing for a

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: joint-ring, nor for measures of lawn, nor for

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: gowns, petticoats, nor caps, nor any petty

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: exhibition; but for the whole world,--why, who would

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: not make her husband a cuckold to make him a

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: monarch? I should venture purgatory for't.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Beshrew me, if I would do such a wrong

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: For the whole world.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Why the wrong is but a wrong i' the world: and

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: having the world for your labour, tis a wrong in your

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: own world, and you might quickly make it right.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I do not think there is any such woman.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Yes, a dozen; and as many to the vantage as would

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: store the world they played for.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: But I do think it is their husbands' faults

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: If wives do fall: say that they slack their duties,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And pour our treasures into foreign laps,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Or else break out in peevish jealousies,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Throwing restraint upon us; or say they strike us,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Or scant our former having in despite;

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Why, we have galls, and though we have some grace,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Yet have we some revenge. Let husbands know

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Their wives have sense like them: they see and smell

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And have their palates both for sweet and sour,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: As husbands have. What is it that they do

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: When they change us for others? Is it sport?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I think it is: and doth affection breed it?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I think it doth: is't frailty that thus errs?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: It is so too: and have not we affections,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Desires for sport, and frailty, as men have?

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Then let them use us well: else let them know,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: EMILIA
line: The ills we do, their ills instruct us so.

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Good night, good night: heaven me such uses send,

scene: SCENE III.  Another room In the castle.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Not to pick bad from bad, but by bad mend!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Here, stand behind this bulk; straight will he come:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Wear thy good rapier bare, and put it home:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Quick, quick; fear nothing; I'll be at thy elbow:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: It makes us, or it mars us; think on that,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: And fix most firm thy resolution.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: Be near at hand; I may miscarry in't.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Here, at thy hand: be bold, and take thy stand.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: I have no great devotion to the deed;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: And yet he hath given me satisfying reasons:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: 'Tis but a man gone. Forth, my sword: he dies.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: I have rubb'd this young quat almost to the sense,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: And he grows angry. Now, whether he kill Cassio,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Or Cassio him, or each do kill the other,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Every way makes my gain: live Roderigo,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: He calls me to a restitution large

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Of gold and jewels that I bobb'd from him,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: As gifts to Desdemona;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: It must not be: if Cassio do remain,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: He hath a daily beauty in his life

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: That makes me ugly; and, besides, the Moor

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: May unfold me to him; there stand I in much peril:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: No, he must die. But so: I hear him coming.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: I know his gait, 'tis he.--Villain, thou diest!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: That thrust had been mine enemy indeed,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: But that my coat is better than thou know'st

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I will make proof of thine.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: O, I am slain!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I am maim'd for ever. Help, ho! murder! murder!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The voice of Cassio: Iago keeps his word.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: O, villain that I am!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It is even so.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: O, help, ho! light! a surgeon!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: 'Tis he:--O brave Iago, honest and just,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That hast such noble sense of thy friend's wrong!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Thou teachest me. Minion, your dear lies dead,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And your unblest fate hies: strumpet, I come.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Forth of my heart those charms, thine eyes, are blotted;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Thy bed, lust-stain'd, shall with lust's blood be spotted.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: What, ho! no watch? no passage? murder! murder!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: 'Tis some mischance; the cry is very direful.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: O, help!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Hark!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: O wretched villain!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Two or three groan: it is a heavy night:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: These may be counterfeits: let's think't unsafe

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: To come in to the cry without more help.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: Nobody come? then shall I bleed to death.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Hark!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Here's one comes in his shirt, with light and weapons.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Who's there? whose noise is this that ones on murder?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: We do not know.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Did not you hear a cry?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Here, here! for heaven's sake, help me!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: What's the matter?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: This is Othello's ancient, as I take it.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: The same indeed; a very valiant fellow.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: What are you here that cry so grievously?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Iago? O, I am spoil'd, undone by villains!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Give me some help.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: O me, lieutenant! what villains have done this?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: I think that one of them is hereabout,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: And cannot make away.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: O treacherous villains!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: What are you there? come in, and give some help.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: O, help me here!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: That's one of them.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: O murderous slave! O villain!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: RODERIGO
line: O damn'd Iago! O inhuman dog!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Kill men i' the dark!--Where be these bloody thieves?--

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: How silent is this town!--Ho! murder! murder!--

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: What may you be? are you of good or evil?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: As you shall prove us, praise us.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Signior Lodovico?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: He, sir.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: I cry you mercy. Here's Cassio hurt by villains.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Cassio!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: How is't, brother!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: My leg is cut in two.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Marry, heaven forbid!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Light, gentlemen; I'll bind it with my shirt.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: BIANCA
line: What is the matter, ho? who is't that cried?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Who is't that cried!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: BIANCA
line: O my dear Cassio! my sweet Cassio! O Cassio,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Cassio, Cassio!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: O notable strumpet! Cassio, may you suspect

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Who they should be that have thus many led you?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: No.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: I am to find you thus: I have been to seek you.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Lend me a garter. So. O, for a chair,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: To bear him easily hence!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: BIANCA
line: Alas, he faints! O Cassio, Cassio, Cassio!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Gentlemen all, I do suspect this trash

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: To be a party in this injury.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Patience awhile, good Cassio. Come, come;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Lend me a light. Know we this face or no?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Alas my friend and my dear countryman

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Roderigo! no:--yes, sure: O heaven! Roderigo.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: What, of Venice?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Even he, sir; did you know him?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Know him! ay.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Signior Gratiano? I cry you gentle pardon;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: These bloody accidents must excuse my manners,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: That so neglected you.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: I am glad to see you.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: How do you, Cassio? O, a chair, a chair!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Roderigo!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: He, he 'tis he.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: O, that's well said; the chair!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Some good man bear him carefully from hence;

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: I'll fetch the general's surgeon.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: For you, mistress,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Save you your labour. He that lies slain

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: here, Cassio,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Was my dear friend: what malice was between you?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: CASSIO
line: None in the world; nor do I know the man.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: To BIANCA  What, look you pale? O, bear him out

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: o' the air.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Stay you, good gentlemen. Look you pale, mistress?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Do you perceive the gastness of her eye?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Nay, if you stare, we shall hear more anon.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Behold her well; I pray you, look upon her:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Do you see, gentlemen? nay, guiltiness will speak,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Though tongues were out of use.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: EMILIA
line: 'Las, what's the matter? what's the matter, husband?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Cassio hath here been set on in the dark

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: By Roderigo and fellows that are scaped:

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: He's almost slain, and Roderigo dead.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Alas, good gentleman! alas, good Cassio!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: This is the fruit of whoring. Prithee, Emilia,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Go know of Cassio where he supp'd to-night.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: What, do you shake at that?

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: BIANCA
line: He supp'd at my house; but I therefore shake not.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: O, did he so? I charge you, go with me.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Fie, fie upon thee, strumpet!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: BIANCA
line: I am no strumpet; but of life as honest

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: BIANCA
line: As you that thus abuse me.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: EMILIA
line: As I! foh! fie upon thee!

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Kind gentlemen, let's go see poor Cassio dress'd.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Come, mistress, you must tell's another tale.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Emilia run you to the citadel,

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: And tell my lord and lady what hath happ'd.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: Will you go on? I pray.

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: This is the night

scene: SCENE I.  Cyprus. A street.
speaker: IAGO
line: That either makes me or fordoes me quite.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It is the cause, it is the cause, my soul,--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Let me not name it to you, you chaste stars!--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It is the cause. Yet I'll not shed her blood;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Nor scar that whiter skin of hers than snow,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And smooth as monumental alabaster.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Yet she must die, else she'll betray more men.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Put out the light, and then put out the light:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: If I quench thee, thou flaming minister,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I can again thy former light restore,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Should I repent me: but once put out thy light,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Thou cunning'st pattern of excelling nature,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I know not where is that Promethean heat

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That can thy light relume. When I have pluck'd the rose,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I cannot give it vital growth again.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It must needs wither: I'll smell it on the tree.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ah balmy breath, that dost almost persuade

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Justice to break her sword! One more, one more.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Be thus when thou art dead, and I will kill thee,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And love thee after. One more, and this the last:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: So sweet was ne'er so fatal. I must weep,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: But they are cruel tears: this sorrow's heavenly;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It strikes where it doth love. She wakes.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Who's there? Othello?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ay. Desdemona.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Will you come to bed, my lord?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Have you pray'd to-night, Desdemona?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Ay, my lord.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: If you bethink yourself of any crime

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Unreconciled as yet to heaven and grace,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Solicit for it straight.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Alas, my lord, what do you mean by that?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Well, do it, and be brief; I will walk by:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I would not kill thy unprepared spirit;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: No; heaven forfend! I would not kill thy soul.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Talk you of killing?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ay, I do.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Then heaven

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Have mercy on me!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Amen, with all my heart!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: If you say so, I hope you will not kill me.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Hum!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And yet I fear you; for you are fatal then

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: When your eyes roll so: why I should fear I know not,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Since guiltiness I know not; but yet I feel I fear.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Think on thy sins.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: They are loves I bear to you.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ay, and for that thou diest.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: That death's unnatural that kills for loving.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Alas, why gnaw you so your nether lip?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Some bloody passion shakes your very frame:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: These are portents; but yet I hope, I hope,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: They do not point on me.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Peace, and be still!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I will so. What's the matter?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That handkerchief which I so loved and gave thee

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Thou gavest to Cassio.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: No, by my life and soul!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Send for the man, and ask him.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Sweet soul, take heed,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Take heed of perjury; thou art on thy deathbed.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Ay, but not yet to die.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Yes, presently:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Therefore confess thee freely of thy sin;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: For to deny each article with oath

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Cannot remove nor choke the strong conception

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That I do groan withal. Thou art to die.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Then Lord have mercy on me!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I say, amen.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: And have you mercy too! I never did

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Offend you in my life; never loved Cassio

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: But with such general warranty of heaven

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: As I might love: I never gave him token.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: By heaven, I saw my handkerchief in's hand.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O perjured woman! thou dost stone my heart,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And makest me call what I intend to do

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: A murder, which I thought a sacrifice:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I saw the handkerchief.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: He found it then;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: I never gave it him: send for him hither;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Let him confess a truth.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: He hath confess'd.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: What, my lord?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That he hath used thee.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: How? unlawfully?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ay.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: He will not say so.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: No, his mouth is stopp'd;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Honest Iago hath ta'en order for't.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: O! my fear interprets: what, is he dead?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Had all his hairs been lives, my great revenge

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Had stomach for them all.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Alas! he is betray'd and I undone.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Out, strumpet! weep'st thou for him to my face?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: O, banish me, my lord, but kill me not!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Down, strumpet!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Kill me to-morrow: let me live to-night!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Nay, if you strive--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: But half an hour!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Being done, there is no pause.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: But while I say one prayer!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It is too late.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Within  My lord, my lord! what, ho! my lord, my lord!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What noise is this? Not dead? not yet quite dead?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I that am cruel am yet merciful;
