scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I would not have thee linger in thy pain: So, so.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Within  What, ho! my lord, my lord!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Who's there?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Within  O, good my lord, I would speak a word with you!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Yes: 'tis Emilia. By and by. She's dead.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: 'Tis like she comes to speak of Cassio's death.--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: The noise was here. Ha! no more moving?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Still as the grave. Shall she come in? were't good?--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I think she stirs again:--no. What's best to do?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: If she come in, she'll sure speak to my wife:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: My wife! my wife! what wife? I have no wife.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O insupportable! O heavy hour!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Methinks it should be now a huge eclipse

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Of sun and moon, and that the affrighted globe

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Should yawn at alteration.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Within  I do beseech you

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: That I may speak with you, O, good my lord!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I had forgot thee: O, come in, Emilia;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Soft; by and by. Let me the curtains draw.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Where art thou?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What's the matter with thee now?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O, my good lord, yonder's foul murders done!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What, now?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: But now, my lord.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It is the very error of the moon;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: She comes more nearer earth than she was wont,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And makes men mad.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Cassio, my lord, hath kill'd a young Venetian

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Call'd Roderigo.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Roderigo kill'd!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And Cassio kill'd!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: No, Cassio is not kill'd.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Not Cassio kill'd! then murder's out of tune,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And sweet revenge grows harsh.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: O, falsely, falsely murder'd!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Alas, what cry is that?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That! what?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Out, and alas! that was my lady's voice.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Help! help, ho! help! O lady, speak again!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Sweet Desdemona! O sweet mistress, speak!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: A guiltless death I die.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O, who hath done this deed?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Nobody; I myself. Farewell

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: DESDEMONA
line: Commend me to my kind lord: O, farewell!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Why, how should she be murder'd?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Alas, who knows?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: You heard her say herself, it was not I.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: She said so: I must needs report the truth.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: She's, like a liar, gone to burning hell:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: 'Twas I that kill'd her.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O, the more angel she,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And you the blacker devil!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: She turn'd to folly, and she was a whore.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Thou dost belie her, and thou art a devil.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: She was false as water.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Thou art rash as fire, to say

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: That she was false: O, she was heavenly true!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Cassio did top her; ask thy husband else.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O, I were damn'd beneath all depth in hell,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: But that I did proceed upon just grounds

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: To this extremity. Thy husband knew it all.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: My husband!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Thy husband.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: That she was false to wedlock?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ay, with Cassio. Nay, had she been true,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: If heaven would make me such another world

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Of one entire and Perfect chrysolite,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I'ld not have sold her for it.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: My husband!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ay, 'twas he that told me first:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: An honest man he is, and hates the slime

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That sticks on filthy deeds.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: My husband!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: What needs this iteration, woman? I say thy husband.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O mistress, villany hath made mocks with love,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: My husband say that she was false!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: He, woman;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I say thy husband: dost understand the word?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: My friend, thy husband, honest, honest Iago.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: If he say so, may his pernicious soul

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Rot half a grain a day! he lies to the heart:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: She was too fond of her most filthy bargain.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ha!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Do thy worst:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: This deed of thine is no more worthy heaven

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Than thou wast worthy her.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Peace, you were best.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Thou hast not half that power to do me harm

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: As I have to be hurt. O gull! O dolt!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: As ignorant as dirt! thou hast done a deed--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I care not for thy sword; I'll make thee known,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Though I lost twenty lives.--Help! help, ho! help!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: The Moor hath kill'd my mistress! Murder! murder!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: MONTANO
line: What is the matter? How now, general!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O, are you come, Iago? you have done well,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: That men must lay their murders on your neck.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: What is the matter?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Disprove this villain, if thou be'st a man:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: He says thou told'st him that his wife was false:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I know thou didst not, thou'rt not such a villain:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Speak, for my heart is full.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: I told him what I thought, and told no more

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: Than what he found himself was apt and true.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: But did you ever tell him she was false?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: I did.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: You told a lie, an odious, damned lie;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Upon my soul, a lie, a wicked lie.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: She false with Cassio!--did you say with Cassio?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: With Cassio, mistress. Go to, charm your tongue.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I will not charm my tongue; I am bound to speak:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: My mistress here lies murder'd in her bed,--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: All
line: O heavens forfend!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And your reports have set the murder on.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Nay, stare not, masters: it is true, indeed.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: 'Tis a strange truth.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: MONTANO
line: O monstrous act!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Villany, villany, villany!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I think upon't, I think: I smell't: O villany!--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I thought so then:--I'll kill myself for grief:--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O villany, villany!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: What, are you mad? I charge you, get you home.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Good gentlemen, let me have leave to speak:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: 'Tis proper I obey him, but not now.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Perchance, Iago, I will ne'er go home.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O! O! O!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Nay, lay thee down and roar;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: For thou hast kill'd the sweetest innocent

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: That e'er did lift up eye.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Rising  O, she was foul!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I scarce did know you, uncle: there lies your niece,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Whose breath, indeed, these hands have newly stopp'd:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I know this act shows horrible and grim.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Poor Desdemona! I am glad thy father's dead:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Thy match was mortal to him, and pure grief

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Shore his old thread in twain: did he live now,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: This sight would make him do a desperate turn,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Yea, curse his better angel from his side,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: And fall to reprobation.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: 'Tis pitiful; but yet Iago knows

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That she with Cassio hath the act of shame

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: A thousand times committed; Cassio confess'd it:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And she did gratify his amorous works

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: With that recognizance and pledge of love

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Which I first gave her; I saw it in his hand:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It was a handkerchief, an antique token

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: My father gave my mother.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O heaven! O heavenly powers!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: Come, hold your peace.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: 'Twill out, 'twill out: I peace!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: No, I will speak as liberal as the north:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Let heaven and men and devils, let them all,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: All, all, cry shame against me, yet I'll speak.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: Be wise, and get you home.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I will not.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Fie!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Your sword upon a woman?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O thou dull Moor! that handkerchief thou speak'st of

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: I found by fortune and did give my husband;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: For often, with a solemn earnestness,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: More than indeed belong'd to such a trifle,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: He begg'd of me to steal it.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: Villanous whore!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: She give it Cassio! no, alas! I found it,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And I did give't my husband.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: Filth, thou liest!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: By heaven, I do not, I do not, gentlemen.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: O murderous coxcomb! what should such a fool

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Do with so good a woman?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Are there no stones in heaven

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: But what serve for the thunder?--Precious villain!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: The woman falls; sure, he hath kill'd his wife.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Ay, ay: O, lay me by my mistress' side.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: He's gone, but his wife's kill'd.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: MONTANO
line: 'Tis a notorious villain. Take you this weapon,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: MONTANO
line: Which I have here recover'd from the Moor:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: MONTANO
line: Come, guard the door without; let him not pass,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: MONTANO
line: But kill him rather. I'll after that same villain,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: MONTANO
line: For 'tis a damned slave.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I am not valiant neither,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: But ever puny whipster gets my sword:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: But why should honour outlive honesty?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Let it go all.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: What did thy song bode, lady?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Hark, canst thou hear me? I will play the swan.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: And die in music.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Willow, willow, willow,--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: Moor, she was chaste; she loved thee, cruel Moor;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: So come my soul to bliss, as I speak true;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: EMILIA
line: So speaking as I think, I die, I die.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I have another weapon in this chamber;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: It is a sword of Spain, the ice-brook's temper:--

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O, here it is. Uncle, I must come forth.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Within  If thou attempt it, it will cost thee dear:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Thou hast no weapon, and perforce must suffer.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Look in upon me then and speak with me,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Or, naked as I am, I will assault thee.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: What is the matter?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Behold, I have a weapon;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: A better never did itself sustain

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Upon a soldier's thigh: I have seen the day,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That, with this little arm and this good sword,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I have made my way through more impediments

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Than twenty times your stop: but, O vain boast!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Who can control his fate? 'tis not so now.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Be not afraid, though you do see me weapon'd;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Here is my journey's end, here is my butt,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And very sea-mark of my utmost sail.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Do you go back dismay'd? 'tis a lost fear;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Man but a rush against Othello's breast,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And he retires. Where should Othello go?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Now, how dost thou look now? O ill-starr'd wench!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Pale as thy smock! when we shall meet at compt,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: This look of thine will hurl my soul from heaven,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: And fiends will snatch at it. Cold, cold, my girl!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Even like thy chastity. O cursed slave!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Whip me, ye devils,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: From the possession of this heavenly sight!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Blow me about in winds! roast me in sulphur!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Wash me in steep-down gulfs of liquid fire!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O Desdemona! Desdemona! dead!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Oh! Oh! Oh!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Where is this rash and most unfortunate man?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: That's he that was Othello: here I am.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Where is that viper? bring the villain forth.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I look down towards his feet; but that's a fable.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: If that thou best a devil, I cannot kill thee.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Wrench his sword from him.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: I bleed, sir; but not kill'd.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I am not sorry neither: I'ld have thee live;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: For, in my sense, 'tis happiness to die.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: O thou Othello, thou wert once so good,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Fall'n in the practise of a damned slave,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: What shall be said to thee?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Why, any thing:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: An honourable murderer, if you will;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: For nought I did in hate, but all in honour.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: This wretch hath part confess'd his villany:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Did you and he consent in Cassio's death?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Ay.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Dear general, I never gave you cause.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: I do believe it, and I ask your pardon.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Will you, I pray, demand that demi-devil

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Why he hath thus ensnared my soul and body?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: Demand me nothing: what you know, you know:

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: IAGO
line: From this time forth I never will speak word.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: What, not to pray?

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: GRATIANO
line: Torments will ope your lips.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: Well, thou dost best.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Sir, you shall understand what hath befall'n,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Which, as I think, you know not. Here is a letter

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Found in the pocket of the slain Roderigo;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: And here another: the one of them imports

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: The death of Cassio to be undertook

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: By Roderigo.

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: OTHELLO
line: O villain!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: CASSIO
line: Most heathenish and most gross!

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Now here's another discontented paper,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Found in his pocket too; and this, it seems,

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: Roderigo meant to have sent this damned villain;

scene: SCENE II.  A bedchamber in the castle: DESDEMONA in bed asleep; a light burning.
speaker: LODOVICO
line: But that belike Iago in the interim
